name: Release v1.5.1
body:
- Optimise for hotspot inlining, #101
- Enable better test coverage, #102

See [release notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v1.5
body:
- Optimise internals of generated builders to use immutable collections, #96
- Provide details of files changed by code generation, to be used by tools, #99
- Standard format for exception messages, to be used by tools, #98
- Add related projects page to website
- Fixed parsing of verbose command line flag. #97

See [release notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v1.4
body:
- Support Optional properties in serialization, #93 
- Support Optional return type for getters of nullable properties, #92 
- Generate serialization version id, #94 
- Add ImmutablePreBuild annotation, #95 
- Avoid including derived properties in equals/hashCode, #91 
- Add support for protected scope getters and setters, #90 

See [release notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v1.3
body:
- Add varargs overrides in immutable builders, #85 
- Fix hash code to avoid degradation when lots of nulls, #89
- Fix handling of wildcard generic fields, #88 
- Fix parsing of field initializers without spaces, #87 
- Fix generation of immutable package scoped beans, #86 

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v1.2
body:
- Add ability to iterate over all the beans within a bean, #84 
- Add ability to declare alias for property, #82 
- Add option to allow property values to be defaulted on immutable beans, #80 
- Add option to allow hash codes to be cached, #79
- Fix parsing of class name with extends clause union types, #83 
- Fix parsing of class name with extends clause generics of type with 2 generic parameters, #81 

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v1.1
body:
- Add JSON round-trip serialization., #75
- Use effective type exposed by Joda-Convert in serialization, #76
- Add @Override annotation on toBuilder(), #73
- Reduce scope of serialization helper classes which should not have been public (incompatibility)

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v1.0.1
body:
- Fix immutable beans with private builders, #70
- Fix immutable builder setString() , #69
- Add JodaBeansUtils.notEmpty(Collection) and JodaBeansUtils.notEmpty(Map), #71

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v1.0
body:
Stable release v1.0:
- Remove Bean.clone(), clashes with generic union types, #66 
- Provide `@ImmutableValidator` to manually validate constructors, #65 
- Add getter/setter style of "field" for direct access to field, #67 
- Block immutable beans from using EnumBiMap, EnumHashBiMap, HashBiMap, EnumMultiset, HashMultiset, LinkedHashMultiset, TreeMultiset, ArrayListMultimap, LinkedListMultimap, HashMultimap, LinkedHashMultimap, TreeMultimap, SortedSetMultimap SparseGrid, DenseGrid. Change Multimap interface to use ArrayListMultimap, not HashMultimap, because ImmutableMultimap is list based, #64.
- Generate Javadoc param tags for generic types in meta/builder, #68

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v0.9.8
body:
- Enhance and fix meta-type support in serialization, #60
- Enhance and fix 2D array support in serialization, #61
- Fix immutable beans builder method comment, #62
- Undo deprecation of BasicImmutableBeanBuilder
- Enable selective use of Override annotation, #63

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v0.9.7
body:
- Add support for Guava BiMap interface, #58
- Add support for Joda-Collect Grid interface, #59
- Add support for Guava Table interface, #54
- Do not clone in getters of mutable beans for arrays and java.util.Date, #57
- Handle collections in clone(), #55
- Add mime types for serialized formats, #56

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v0.9.6
body:
- Immutable subclass builders do not work, #53
- Bean builder should have getters, #52
- Deprecate BasicImmutableBeanBuilder
- Support three generic parameters, #51

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v0.9.4
body:
- Add Joda-Bean binary serialization based on MessagePack, #49
- More flexible XML parsing wrt Joda-Convert, #50
- Invalid code generated for an abstract @ImmutableBean #48
- Guava MultiSet serialized incorrectly, #47

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v0.9.3
body:
- Choose known types in serialization carefully, #46 
- Fix BeanComparisonError, #45

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v0.9.2
body:
- Handle refactored beans in deserialization, #43 
- Handle type renames in deserialization, #40
- Remove encodeClass/decodeClass from main serialization API, #44
- BasicBeanBuilder get(String) returns builder rather than the requested data, #42 
- Ensure XML reader property closed, #41
- Short types flag not being used in JodaBeanSer #39 

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

Please use v0.9.3, not this release.

name: Release v0.9.1
body:
- Fix immutable collection copies to preserve comparators. Affects SortedSet and SortedMap, #37
- Remove incorrect suppress unchecked in immutable generic beans, #38

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v0.9.0
body:
- Support partially final beans and immutable subclasses, #24
- Recreate XMLInputFactory each time due to JDK bug JDK-8028111, #36
- Fix to ensure nested class constructors are private if the type is final, #35 
- Extend notNull validation to collection properties, #34 
- Enhance PropertyStyle. Add isReadOnly(), #33
- Add 'equalIgnoring' utility to compare two beans ignoring one or more properties, #32

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v0.8.6
body:
- XML generation of beans with no fields broken in compact mode #30 
- FlexiMap should retain the order of properties #31 

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Release v0.8.5
body:
- Allow beans to have two generic type parameters #21 
- Various bug fixes #26 #27 

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Version 0.8.4
body:
- Handle arrays better
- Allow immutable beans to have a private builder
- Better handling of nullable fields
- Fix various bugs

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Version 0.8.1
body:
- Enhance XML format
- Allow private getters/setter via PropertyDefinition
- Fix Javadoc generation for immutable builder method with generics

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)

name: Version 0.8
body:
- Immutable beans
- XML round trip serialization

See [change notes](http://www.joda.org/joda-beans/changes-report.html)
